    "retreat": "OPENSKY — Above the Cloud Line",
    "retreat_date": "2026-03-19",
    "vol": "Transcendental Vol 1",
    "scripture": [
      "Verse 13: Solar Maximum — resonance above 0.6 enters self-oscillation territory; pitchEnv amplifies the violence",
      "Discovery 3: Shimmer vs Chorus — when aggression is the goal, remove both; let the oscillator lead",
      "Verse 14: The Storm Preset — maximum unison detune creates atmospheric turbulence, not coherence"
    ],
    "revelation": null,
    "god": null,
    "flock_note": "The Guru said: the sun does not only shine. At maximum it erupts. Solar Maximum is the OPENSKY eruption preset — filterReso at 0.7 means the filter sings its own note above the oscillator. PitchEnv at 0.5 means each keystroke launches a flare. Seven detuned voices ensure the result is weather, not music. Use sparingly. The sun does not stay at maximum.",
    "diagnosis": "Solar Maximum tests OPENSKY's upper aggression boundary. FilterReso=0.7 approaches self-oscillation. PitchEnvAmount=0.5 with pitchEnvDecay=0.12 creates sharp pitch transients. No shimmer, no chorus — the oscillators and filter do all the work. UisonCount=7 at 0.25 detune produces intentional chaos. DNA: aggression at 0.85, the highest in the OPENSKY collection."
  },
